{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Automorphic Forms on GL(2)''}}
'''''Automorphic Forms on GL(2)''''' is a book by {{harvs|txt|first=H. |last=Jacquet|authorlink=H. Jacquet|first2=Robert |last2=Langlands|author2-link=Robert Langlands|year=1970}} where they rewrite Hecke's theory of modular forms in terms of the representation theory of GL(2) over [[local field]]s and adele rings of [[global field]]s. A second volume by {{harvs|txt|last=Jacquet|year=1972}} gives an interpretation of some results by Rankin and Selberg in terms of the representation theory of GL(2)&nbsp;×&nbsp;GL(2).

